ocr_full_text_page: READ RIGHT INSTITUTE BY SYED TAIMOOR BUKHARI Date :......... / ......... /20 ....... MOTOWOTOFOSI Fourthly, tangible measures need to be made to meet the digital divide. Education is universal today and accessible online for free. Governments must take actions to curb this divide. In Pakistan, there are NGOS like "Teletaleem" which is working for the provision of education in for flung areas. Government must launch such initiatives as well as build the public-private partnership in order to streamline the process Fifthly, there is dire need to enforce the protection laws and International goals that ensure woman protection and education. The United Nations- Sustainable Development Goals (SDGS) for 2030 preses on the issue of female education. In SDC: 4 there is goal to ensure free education and education rights for all genders without any discrimination . similarly in Pakistan, there are constitutional safeguards that protect woman
